Package: gscan2pdf
Architecture: all
Depends: libgtk2-perl (>= 1:1.090-1), libgtk2-ex-simple-list-perl, libglib-perl (>= 1.100-1), liblocale-gettext-perl (>= 1.05), libsane (>= 1.0.17), sane-utils, libtiff-tools, libpdf-api2-perl, libconfig-general-perl, perlmagick, imagemagick, librsvg2-common
Recommends: libgtk2-ex-podviewer-perl, sane, xdg-utils, djvulibre-bin, unpaper, gocr, tesseract-ocr
Description: A GUI to produce PDFs from scanned documents
 Only two clicks are required to scan several pages and then save all or a
 selection as a PDF or DjVu file, including metadata if required.
 .
 gscan2pdf can control regular or sheet-fed (ADF) scanners with SANE via
 scanimage or scanadf, and can scan multiple pages at once. It presents a
 thumbnail view of scanned pages, and permits simple operations such as rotating
 and deleting pages. 
 .
 PDF conversion is done by PDF::API2.
 .
 The resulting document may be saved as a PDF, DjVu, multipage TIFF file, or
 single page image file.
 .
 The gscan2pdf homepage is http://gscan2pdf.sourceforge.net/
